gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: PHYSIOGRAPHY_SR61_IN is a polygon shapefile that shows the physiographic regions of Indiana. Detailed descriptions of these regions can be obtained from Gray, H.H., 2000, Physiographic Divisions of Indiana, Special Report 61, Indiana Geological Survey.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: PHYSIOGRAPHY_SR61_IN provides a delineation of the currently accepted physiographic regions of Indiana. The information is to be used at a scale of 1:500,000 or smaller.

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: No sliver polygons or dangling nodes.
PHYSIOGRAPHY_SR61_IN contains all physiographic regions of Indiana, as found in Special Report 61.
Physiographic region lines and label attributes were plotted and checked for accuracy by Henry H. Gray and employees of the Indiana Geological Survey against the original paper map.
Information was compiled for publication at a scale of 1:500,000.
The vertical positional accuracy was not a factor in the digital production of this dataset. No quantitative tests were performed.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: The dataset PHYSIO was brought into ArcInfo using the SHAPEARC command. After a CLEAN and BUILD, the arcs were projected from NAD 27 to decimal degrees. The decimal degree projection was then reprojected into NAD 83.

The original coverage, PHYSIO_83, was clipped to another coverage, INCLP83, containing the area within the 92 county boundaries for the state of Indiana, which was compiled at a scale of 1:24,000. Since PHYSIO_83 and INCLP83 boundaries did not coincide perfectly with one another, some polygons along the state boundary were either slightly truncated or slightly extended to the new boundary. In every case, the modifications were minor. The resulting coverage was converted to a shapefile named PHYSIOGRAPHY_SR61_IN. Special Report 61 was also used to attribute the shapefile named PHYSIOGRAPHY_SR61_IN, to more closely resemble the paper map.

This metadata was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit) and MP (Metadata Parser) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (United States Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."
Physiographic divisions of Indiana polygons and attributes.
